Vietnamese Sentiment Analysis using PhoBERT

This project is a deep learning-based Vietnamese sentiment analysis system using PhoBERT (Transformer model) fine-tuned on a labeled dataset.

It classifies text into 3 sentiment categories:

😞 Negative
😐 Neutral
😄 Positive
🧠 Model Overview

The project uses:

PhoBERT (vinai/phobert-base)
Hugging Face Transformers
PyTorch
Fine-tuning on Vietnamese sentiment dataset

Compared to traditional ML methods (TF-IDF + classical models), PhoBERT provides better understanding of Vietnamese context.

📊 Dataset

Input format:

content	label
sản phẩm rất tốt	2
bình thường	1
quá tệ	0

Label mapping:

0 → Negative
1 → Neutral
2 → Positive
⚠️ Data Imbalance

The dataset is imbalanced:

Positive : 20093  
Negative : 6669  
Neutral  : 4698  

This causes lower performance on the Neutral class.

⚙️ Preprocessing

Steps:

Lowercasing text
Removing URLs, special characters, numbers
Tokenizing Vietnamese text using underthesea
Encoding labels
🏋️ Training

To train the model:

python main.py
Training configuration:
Model: PhoBERT base
Max length: 128
Batch size: 8
Epochs: 3
Trainer API (Hugging Face)
📈 Performance

Example evaluation results:

Accuracy: ~0.80

Positive F1-score: 0.90  
Negative F1-score: 0.77  
Neutral F1-score: 0.35  

Model performs well on Positive and Negative classes but struggles with Neutral due to imbalance.

🧪 Inference (Testing)

Run prediction script:

python test_predict.py

Example:

from predict import predict_sentiment

print(predict_sentiment("Sản phẩm rất đẹp, mình rất hài lòng"))
# Positive
📦 Installation
pip install -r requirements.txt

Main dependencies:

transformers
torch
scikit-learn
pandas
underthesea
